display="inline"><![CDATA[z\in \mathbb {C}]]></fr:tex>, <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[z\neq 0]]></fr:tex>, there exists a unique complex number denoted <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[z^{-1}]]></fr:tex> such that <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[zz^{-1}=1]]></fr:tex>. Moreover, if <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[z=x+\mathrm {i} y]]></fr:tex> with <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[x,y\in \mathbb {R}]]></fr:tex>, then
<fr:tex
display="block"><![CDATA[z^{-1}=\frac {x}{x^{2}+y^{2}}+\mathrm {i}\frac {-y}{x^{2}+y^{2}}]]></fr:tex></fr:p>
 
   
