display="inline"><![CDATA[z_{2}\in \mathbb {C}]]></fr:tex> be complex numbers. Then the following all hold:</fr:p><fr:ol><fr:li><fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\overline {z_{1}+z_{2}}=\overline {z_{1}}+\overline {z_{2}}]]></fr:tex> (the conjugate of the sum is the sum of conjugates)</fr:li>
<fr:li><fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\overline {z_{1}z_{2}}=\overline {z_{1}}\overline {z_{2}}]]></fr:tex> (the conjugate of products is the product of conjugates)</fr:li>
<fr:li><fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\overline {1/z_{1}}=1/\overline {z_{1}}]]></fr:tex> when <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[z_{1}\neq 0]]></fr:tex></fr:li>
<fr:li><fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\overline {z_{1}}=z_{1}]]></fr:tex> if and only if <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\Im (z_{1})=0]]></fr:tex></fr:li>
<fr:li><fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\overline {\overline {z_{1}}}=z_{1}]]></fr:tex></fr:li>
